{"by":"justinmayer","id":47765780,"kids":[47766153],"parent":47763759,"text":"Many folks aren’t aware that there is also an open-source, cross-platform desktop GUI application for Jujutsu called GG: <a href=\"https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;gulbanana&#x2F;gg\" rel=\"nofollow\">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;gulbanana&#x2F;gg</a><p>I mention it because while the <i>jj</i> command line interface is excellent, there are certain tasks that I find easier to perform with a graphical user interface. For example, I often want to quickly tap on various revisions and see their diffs. GG makes that kind of repository browsing — and certain squash operations — much more efficient for me.<p>If you’re interested in more information about GG, my co-host and I talked about it in a recent episode of the Abstractions podcast at about the 8:17 mark: <a href=\"https:&#x2F;&#x2F;shows.arrowloop.com&#x2F;@abstractions&#x2F;episodes&#x2F;052-they-deserve-the-dunks\" rel=\"nofollow\">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;shows.arrowloop.com&#x2F;@abstractions&#x2F;episodes&#x2F;052-they-...</a>","time":1776175284,"type":"comment"}